body:
As far as I know, the quantity of lint rules is about 98. You tell me that I need to provide the specific lint rule to you. Hence I take the rule from spyglass lint, named W88, which flags memories where all their elements are not set in the design. Here is the code for the example :
module test(in1, in2, out1);
i```
nput [3:0] in1, in2;
output [3:0] out1;
reg [3:0] out1;
reg [7:0] mem [0:3];
always@(in1) begin
out1 = in1 & in2;
mem[0] = {in1, out1};
mem[2] ={in1, in2};
end
endmodule
```
